It is now 1995, and late into it for that matter, so you may not see the
value of having any new Spear of Destiny levels! Why should anyone spend 
time making any new ones when we now have DOOM, DOOM II, HERETIC, Rise of
The Triad and Dark Forces!? I have all of those too! I decided to have some
fun with the forgotten classic because I am tired of spending money for
every new game that comes along and as an experiment I decided to see
if Spear could be as much fun as it originally was- it is! I have used all
the undocumented features that I could to make this set of levels different 
from any of the originals and all others in existence! You will see ghost
dogs in one of the secret levels. Force fields exist that you can see 
through but not walk through. My NAZIS are not static therefore they are
unpredicatable! Have you noticed how the "better" games still have enemies
that you know exactly where they will appear? You won't get the repeat play
with my new Spear levels as you experience in the more "advanced" games! I
do have guards that still stay and mind their posts but many patrols are
loose too! Those doors you hear slamming aren't hollow sound effects but
actual guards seeking the invading schweinehund! I made the levels compact
and not overly wandering BUT still challenging! You will notice that some
locked doors exist that you can't open with either key- these are guards
that wish to be left alone and they will make their appearance in all due
time! If you set the skill level for one then even your kid sister should
even be able to play. Skill level one has no dogs to kill nor assaulting
mutants but edge up to skill level three and you will have an ordeal that
the neo-phyte will not be able to handle. Go to skill level four and you
will see that I pulled out all the stops- you had better become a miser of
chicken dinners and ammunition if you expect to make it through! These 
levels are my ninth configuration in working out bugs such as hard to see
guards or things blocking your view (such as ammo). By the way did I mention
that one must watch their back while playing at higher skill levels- this
would probably be a good idea also on skill level one in some areas!
 

This is FREEWARE. If you don't like the levels, you are free to change them
to your tastes and I will not be insulted- you'll still be using my 
creativity as a foundation! I have downloaded other levels that are totally
un-realistic and most important- un-playable! I do not have 50 mutants 
