Here is a suggestion that you can use to make changing your gamemaps and
mapheads a lot less painful. Before you install my files in your Spear of
Destiny, copy your GAMEMAPS.SOD and MAPHEAD.SOD to a floppy. Now is 
the neat trick. If you collect a lot of maps, as I do, copy them to their
own sub-directories and add these two custom files to each subdirectory:

 COPY *.SOD %1 <Y.TXT (Name and save this one liner as SWAP.BAT)
 Y   (Name and save this one character as Y.TXT)

If you placed these two files in every subdirectory that have maps, then
all you have to do to change missions is to exit your game, put in the disk
with your files in the appropriate floppy drive and log to the subdirectory
with your desired mission files. Follow me so far!? Now let us assume that
your Spear of Destiny is on your C:\ drive in \SPEAR or C:\SPEAR, you need
to only type on the DOS command line  SWAP C:\SPEAR and your files are 
copied to your Spear of Destiny game without any error or "do you want to
overwrite" prompts because the Y.TXT file answers for you!

If you really want to be slick and save space you can pkzip your two files,
run the zip2exe program on the archive to make it self extracting and embed
it in the SWAP.BAT instead. Let us say you named your self extracting file
FORTRESS.EXE all you have to do to make a proper SWAP.BAT is:

FORTRESS.EXE -O -D %1  (Save as SWAP.BAT of course) The -O is the letter O
not the numeral 0. 

When you run this, instead of the copy command, pkzip will do the right 
stuff without any further input. You still use the SWAP C:\SPEAR entry 
though!

Here is one much coveted "Cheat Code" that is not widely known. If you
purchased the CD-ROM version of Spear of Destiny put out by FormGen you are
undoubtedly ticked at being a victim of a documentation check as a form of
copy protection. You know the routine! Apogee has released Spear of Destiny
without the copy protection- for those that are possessors of the earlier
FormGen version- just type SNOOPS at the documentation check and stop 
fumbling for your manual. If you have seen the movie War Games then you 
might type JOSHUA at the documentation check just for the fun of it! 
You can also make a simple batch file and call it BACKDOOR and have it load
Spear for you and bypass all the opening screens!

ECHO OFF
CLS
SPEAR -DEBUGMODE -NORMAL -TEDLEVEL

Save as BACKDOOR.BAT and your Spear will bypass the documentation check
altogether, put you in debugmode, have you in the bring 'em on skill level,
and on floor one! (You still have to activate using the LEFT SHIFT, LEFT ALT
and Backspace keys.)

